Civil society and subnational governments did not stand still in the face of these trends. In addition to the lawsuits over Guard deployments and protest brutality, a coalition of 282 former Justice Department officials issued a letter warning that the administration was undermining DOJ integrity by violating court orders and dismantling anti-corruption units. Governors Pritzker and Newsom threatened to leave the National Governors Association if it did not address federal troop deployments, and Oklahoma\'92s Republican governor, Kevin Stitt, publicly criticized the deployment of Texas Guard troops to Illinois, marking a rare intra-party rebuke on federalism grounds. In Chicago, Mayor Brandon Johnson signed executive orders prohibiting ICE from using city-owned property as staging areas, asserting local control over federal operations. Protesters shut down Michigan Avenue in a large, peaceful march, and organizers planned a \'93No Kings\'94 protest for the following week, even as House Republicans labeled it terrorism and a \'93Hate America rally.\'94 Resistance remained visible, if outgunned.\
