Abroad, the administration\'92s approach to power and law showed similar patterns. Trump issued an ultimatum to Hamas to accept his Gaza peace plan by a fixed deadline, then announced that Israel and Hamas had agreed to the first phase, including hostage releases and military withdrawal. The U.S. prepared to send 200 troops to Israel to support the ceasefire. At the same time, Trump halted diplomatic outreach with Venezuela and leaned into military options, while ordering the strike on the Colombian boat. The administration announced a $20 billion currency swap framework with Argentina\'92s central bank three weeks before its midterm elections, raising questions about U.S. influence on foreign democratic processes. It also agreed to allow Qatar to establish an air force base at Mountain Home Air Base in Idaho, training Qatari pilots over U.S. airspace, even as Attorney General Bondi\'92s past work as a Qatari agent and Trump\'92s personal business ties to Qatar cast a shadow over the decision. The same themes\'97personal ties, opaque deals, and military leverage\'97ran through foreign policy as well.\
